  "_comment_maintainers": "Bundled FDM printer profiles. Keep keys stable (lowercase, dash-separated: maker-model-nozzle). To extend: add a new entry preserving the schema. `printer_label` MUST start with the maker word (e.g. 'Bambu', 'Prusa', 'Creality', 'Anycubic', 'Elegoo', 'Sovol', 'Snapmaker', 'FlashForge', 'Voron') because the UI splits maker/model on the first word. `grams_per_minute` is a coarse throughput hint used for ETA; tune from real prints when possible. `build_volume` is in millimetres [X, Y, Z]. `layer_height_mm` and `process_label` describe the nozzle's default process. Stick to common nozzles (0.2/0.4/0.6/0.8); aliases like Ender's stock 0.4 are encoded as a single 0.4 entry. Order matters: within a maker the first listed model is what the picker selects when the user switches maker, so put the flagship/most-common model first.",
